        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 18 at 2:35PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>HAZARDS...A band of heavy snow which can rapidly reduce visibility to
less than a quarter of a mile. This band of heavy snow is producing
extremely heavy snow at the rate of 1 to 2 inches per hour and will
be moving through Glenwood Canyon to Dotsero through 2 pm mde.

LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 234 PM MDT, a band of heavy snow was 7
miles east of Glenwood Springs moving east at 15 MPH.

LOCATIONS IMPACTED...
This band of heavy snow will remain over mainly rural areas of
central Central Colorado River Basin, southeastern Flat Tops and
northwestern Gore and Elk Mountains/Central Mountain Valleys
Counties.

This includes Interstate 70 in Colorado between mile markers 120 and
136.

SAFETY INFO...
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Slow down and allow extra
time to reach your destination.
</description>
